    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im having a bit of a hard time w my dev team. we keep getting these random feature requests from stakeholders right in the middle of our sprints and it's totally messing up our velocity. what are some actual ways to manage scope creep so this stops happening? thanks",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Managing scope creep is a common challenge in Agile development. One effective approach is to establish clear goals and objectives for each sprint, and communicate these to stakeholders to set clear expectations. Also, consider using the ' Principle of Constraints' (PoC), which involves focusing on delivering the 'critical velocity' of the project, versus the maximum achievable velocity.\n\nAdditionally, consider using 'scope limits' in your sprint goals, this helps to avoid taking on non-essential features and teams are able to decide which features get the most priority.",
